wdi2-SP.RUR.TOTL.ZS.def: Rural population refers to people living in rural areas as defined by national statistical offices. It is calculated as the difference between total population and urban population.
wdi2-SP.RUR.TOTL.ZS.name: Rural population
wdi2-SP.RUR.TOTL.ZS.source: World Bank staff estimates based on the United Nations Population Division's World Urbanization Prospects: 2018 Revision.
